    "macroSummary": "Risk-on sentiment is driving a coordinated relief rally across asset classes as US-Iran diplomatic hopes reduce geopolitical premiums, weakening the dollar and pressuring oil lower. The peace talk optimism is creating classic intermarket rotation from safe havens into risk assets, with Asian markets leading and commodity volatility declining from panic levels.",
    "regimeImpact": "The diplomatic breakthrough reinforces the oversold relief rally thesis as geopolitical risk premiums unwind, but the bear market structure remains intact until we see sustained breaks above key technical levels.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR ladder closely as BTC approaches $76K resistance with whale accumulation accelerating - consider rolling up strikes on any sustained break above $75K",
      "Reduce short book exposure selectively as relief rally gains momentum, but maintain core positions in Maturity names vulnerable to higher rates",
      "Watch oil's decline toward $85.35 target as geopolitical premium unwinds - stagflation concerns ease if crude holds below $100"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Dollar at 6-week lows signals broad risk-on rotation that typically supports crypto and growth assets in relief rallies.",
      "Oil's shift from panic to cautious stance removes stagflation pressure and supports multiple expansion across risk assets.",
      "BTC whale accumulation hitting 2-month highs at resistance suggests institutional conviction despite ETF flow volatility.",
      "Asian markets leading at 6-week highs indicates global risk appetite recovery that could extend relief rally duration."
    ]
